excerpt: Riders take in coastline views from air-conditioned gondolas on this wheel that lights up nightly.
detail_description: Experience the breathtaking views of downtown Myrtle Beach from a new perspective at the SkyWheel Myrtle Beach. This iconic 187-foot-tall Ferris wheel offers 42 air-conditioned gondolas, providing riders with a bird's-eye view of the Atlantic Ocean, coastline, boardwalk, and downtown area. The nightly illumination adds to the enchanting experience as you take in the beauty of Myrtle Beach from high above during three revolutions that last about 10 minutes.
name: SkyWheel Myrtle Beach
address: 1110 N Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Marine life attraction with kid-friendly exhibits & dive tours, plus live shows & a gift shop.
detail_description: Ripley's Aquarium of Myrtle Beach is an 85,000-square-foot marine life attraction located in the Broadway at the Beach entertainment complex. It offers a variety of kid-friendly exhibits, dive tours, live shows, and a gift shop. Visitors can immerse themselves in the depths of the ocean and encounter bizarre glowing jellyfish, sharp-toothed predators, quirky penguins, and mystical green sea turtles.
name: Ripley's Aquarium of Myrtle Beach
address: 1110 Celebrity Cir, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Beachfront amusement & water park featuring various rides, slides, games & a Ferris wheel.
detail_description: Family Kingdom Amusement Park is a beachfront attraction in Myrtle Beach, offering a variety of rides, games, and a Ferris wheel. The park features 38 rides suitable for kids, families, and thrill-seekers alike. From classic wooden rollercoasters to modern swings and slingshots, there's something for everyone. Visitors can opt for unlimited ride wristbands or single ride tickets. With onsite parking available, the park provides a festive carnival atmosphere perfect for families and couples.
name: Family Kingdom Amusement Park
address: 300 4th Ave S, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Daily performances of tunes from a variety of genres in a large theater boasting high-tech effects.
detail_description: Located in Myrtle Beach, The Carolina Opry Theater offers daily performances featuring a variety of music genres in a large theater with high-tech effects. Since its first show in 1986, it has become the premier entertainment destination in the area. With annual programs like The Christmas Show of the South and concerts from visiting stars, this 2,200-seat venue is a must-visit for live music enthusiasts.
name: The Carolina Opry Theater
address: 8901 N Kings Hwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29572, USA

excerpt: Spacious seasonal water park featuring 30+ rides from a 10-story water slide to a lazy river.
detail_description: Myrtle Waves Water Park is the largest water park in South Carolina, offering over 30 rides and attractions spread across its 20-acre space. Visitors can experience the thrill of towering water slides, relax in a massive wave pool, or enjoy a leisurely float along the 330,000-gallon lazy river. The park also features play areas for kids and amenities like picnic areas and dining options at Island Cafe and Sharkeys Snack Shack.
name: Myrtle Waves Water Park
address: 3000 Mr. Joe White Ave, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Broadway at the Beach is a renowned destination in Myrtle Beach, known for its entertainment and shopping options. This expansive 350-acre area has been a popular attraction since its establishment in 1995. Situated on Celebrity Circle, it offers a plethora of activities and retail opportunities at the heart of Myrtle Beach.
name: The beach
address: 3250 Nash St, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Myrtle Beach, a city and vacation resort on South Carolina’s Atlantic coast, is the hub of the Grand Strand, a 60-mile string of beaches. It’s also known for its celebrity-designed golf courses. Along its beachfront boardwalk are arcades, souvenir stands and restaurants, as well as the old-fashioned Family Kingdom amusement park and the SkyWheel, one of the country’s tallest Ferris wheels.
detail_description: Myrtle Beach, located on the Atlantic coast of South Carolina, is a popular vacation destination known for its 60-mile stretch of beaches and celebrity-designed golf courses. The beachfront boardwalk offers arcades, souvenir stands, restaurants, an old-fashioned amusement park called Family Kingdom, and the SkyWheel Ferris wheel. Visitors can enjoy various activities such as surfing or relaxing by the private community pool.
name: Myrtle Beach
address: South Carolina, USA

excerpt: Wooden pedestrian path with an oceanside park, retail shops, restaurants & summertime live music.
detail_description: The Myrtle Beach Boardwalk and Promenade is a charming wooden pathway that spans 1.2 miles along the oceanfront, offering a delightful mix of an oceanside park, retail shops, restaurants, and live music during the summer. Visitors can enjoy various attractions such as the SkyWheel Myrtle Beach, Nightmare Haunted House, and the Sling Shot Thrill Ride without paying an admission fee.
name: Myrtle Beach Boardwalk and Promenade
address: South Carolina 29577, USA

detail_description: The Myrtle Beach Pelicans is a minor league baseball team affiliated with the Chicago Cubs, offering game tickets starting at $8. They have various promotions on game days, such as BOGO hot dogs and $1 draft beers. Established in 1999, the team provides an enjoyable experience for both locals and tourists. The stadium is family-friendly with free parking and affordable seats at $20 per person.
name: Myrtle Beach Pelicans
address: 1251 21st Ave N, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Step back in time to the 11th century at Medieval Times Dinner & Tournament in Myrtle Beach. This immersive experience takes you to Her Majesty's Castle, where knights compete in jousting and sword fighting to protect the throne. Upon arrival, you'll be designated a knight to support with a specific colored crown. The evening begins with a Call to Table in the Grand Ceremonial Arena followed by a lavish four-course feast and an exhilarating two-hour tournament.
name: Medieval Times Dinner & Tournament
address: 2904 Fantasy Way, Myrtle Beach, SC 29579, USA

excerpt: Attraction with 100+ hands-on science exhibits plus laser tag, a ropes course & a 6D motion ride.
detail_description: WonderWorks Myrtle Beach is an upside-down building at Broadway at the Beach that offers a unique blend of entertainment and education. It features over 100 hands-on exhibits, including a roller coaster simulator and adventure areas with laser tag and ropes courses. Visitors can enjoy interactive wonder zones that bring scientific concepts to life, such as the Bubble Lab and the Astronaut Training Gyro. The attraction also includes outdoor activities like a zip line and a three-level ropes course in the Soar + Explore area.
name: WonderWorks Myrtle Beach
address: 1313 Celebrity Cir, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Sandy parkland offering recreational oceanfront, a nature center, forested areas & campgrounds.
detail_description: Myrtle Beach State Park is a serene coastal retreat located on the Grand Strand, offering a range of recreational activities and natural attractions. Visitors can enjoy fishing, swimming, camping, and picnicking amidst wide open beaches and an oceanfront maritime forest. The park also hosts various engaging programs such as shark truth discovery, sea turtle patrols, crab catching, snake feeding sessions, forest legends exploration, and more.
name: Myrtle Beach State Park
address: 4401 S Kings Hwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29575, USA

excerpt: Swashbuckling, Blackbeard-themed pirate performances with stunts, plus a 4-course dinner.
detail_description: Pirates Voyage Dinner & Show is a thrilling high-seas adventure that offers a unique dining and entertainment experience for the whole family. Produced by Dolly Parton, this show features swashbuckling pirates, ships, cannons, mermaids, seals, parrots, and divers on an underwater stage. Guests can enjoy a 4-course Caribbean-themed dinner while watching the dynamic performance unfold before them. Kids have the opportunity to interact with performers and dress up as pirates during the show.
name: Pirates Voyage Dinner & Show
address: 8907 N Kings Hwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29572, USA

excerpt: Storefront shops open into an enclosed area with dining, movies, bowling, bike rentals & a theater.
detail_description: The Market Common in Myrtle Beach is a vibrant mixed-use neighborhood with a variety of shops, dining options, and entertainment. Situated on the former Air Force base grounds, this trendy area offers unique boutiques, bars, restaurants, and a movie theater. Throughout the year, visitors can enjoy free events such as Movies Under the Stars, art festivals, New Year's Eve celebrations, and complimentary carriage rides.
name: The Market Common - Myrtle Beach
address: 4017 Deville St, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: A museum outpost featuring celebrity wax figures, a souvenir store, a zombie lab & a mirror maze.
detail_description: The Hollywood Wax Museum in Myrtle Beach is a fun and entertaining attraction that pays tribute to pop culture. This museum features lifelike wax figures of famous celebrities from the modern era of movies, music, TV, and sports. Visitors can take selfies with their favorite stars such as Marilyn Monroe, Justin Timberlake, and Katy Perry. The museum also offers a souvenir store, a zombie lab experience, and a mirror maze for added entertainment.
name: Hollywood Wax Museum
address: 1808 21st Ave N unit a, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Indoor/outdoor recreation complex with 7 go-kart tracks, rock climbing, tot rides & mini-golf.
detail_description: Located in Myrtle Beach, Broadway Grand Prix is an indoor/outdoor recreation complex that offers a variety of activities for visitors. The highlight of the park is its seven go-kart tracks, suitable for all ages and skill levels. From the fastest Grand Prix Pro Track to the Kid's Track and KidZone, there are options for everyone.
name: Broadway Grand Prix
address: 1820 21st Ave N, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Shopping-mall chain featuring a variety of brand-name & designer outlet stores.
detail_description: Tanger Outlets Myrtle Beach Hwy 501 is a shopper's paradise, offering an impressive selection of brand-name and designer outlet stores. Located conveniently along Highway 501, this vibrant shopping destination caters to every fashionista's needs with a diverse range of specialty shops. From trendy apparel at Adidas and Nine West Outlet to stylish accessories from Michael Kors and Ecco, you'll find everything you need for your beach getaway or everyday wear.
name: Tanger Outlets Myrtle Beach Hwy 501
address: 4635 Factory Stores Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29579, USA

detail_description: Pavilion Park, the largest amusement park in Myrtle Beach, is a nostalgic tribute to the beloved Myrtle Beach Pavilion. Located at Broadway at the Beach, this park features classic rides from the old Pavilion Amusement Park. Divided into Fun Park and Action Park, it offers attractions for toddlers, kids, and those seeking a more relaxed theme park experience.
name: Pavilion Park
address: 205 9th Ave N, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Contemporary shopping center features popular chain retailers, restaurants & a movie theater.
detail_description: Located in Myrtle Beach, Coastal Grand Mall is a contemporary shopping center that offers a traditional mall experience with popular chain retailers, restaurants, and a movie theater. With over 100 well-known brand stores including anchor stores like Dick's Sporting Goods and Belk, it provides a wide variety of shopping options. The all-American food court is perfect for grabbing a mid-shopping snack, and the mall also offers extended holiday hours for last-minute gifts.
name: Coastal Grand Mall
address: 2000 Coastal Grand Cir, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Celebrity look-a-likes perform hit songs, complete with backup dancers & dramatic stage lighting.
detail_description: Legends in Concert Theater Myrtle Beach is a renowned live tribute show featuring celebrity look-alikes performing hit songs with backup dancers and dramatic stage lighting. With over 30 years of entertaining audiences, the theater boasts a collection of live tribute artists who not only resemble but also sound like the stars they portray. The performers undergo extensive practice to perfect their craft, paying attention to every detail from choreography to hair, makeup, and mannerisms.
name: Legends in Concert Theater Myrtle Beach
address: 2925 Hollywood Dr, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Visual-arts exhibits, including a collection of Southern works, plus a library & classroom space.
detail_description: The Franklin G. Burroughs-Simeon B. Chapin Art Museum in Myrtle Beach aims to be a top visual arts museum in the Carolinas, offering 11 galleries with changing exhibitions throughout the year. The museum showcases a diverse range of art forms including paintings, textiles, sculpture, photography, video, ceramics and more. Visitors can also enjoy engaging programming such as artist receptions, tours, lectures and workshops for all ages.
name: Franklin G. Burroughs-Simeon B. Chapin Art Museum
address: 3100 S Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Public Beach in Myrtle Beach is a must-visit destination for families and beach lovers. It offers a clean and friendly environment, making it one of the cleanest and most pleasant beaches to visit. Visitors can enjoy the beautiful coastline without any issues or trash in sight. However, it's important to be aware of your surroundings, especially regarding potential jellyfish encounters. Additionally, staying at a resort or gated property is recommended due to concerns about crime and drug use in the area after sunset.
name: Public Beach
address: Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Landscaped miniature golf with 2 18-hole course options, an ocean-view lookout & a snack bar/patio.
detail_description: Jungle Lagoon Miniature Golf is a landscaped mini-golf destination in North Myrtle Beach, offering two 18-hole course options. The outdoor course features roaring waterfalls and exotic critter statues like gorillas, elephants, giraffes, and tropical birds. Visitors can enjoy an ocean-view lookout and grab snacks at the on-site snack bar/patio. The courses are suitable for families with kids as they are well-lit and not too scary.
name: Jungle Lagoon Miniature Golf
address: 404 5th Ave S, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: The Myrtle Beach Pinball Museum is a fun and interactive attraction located in the Market Common district of Myrtle Beach. For a small fee, visitors can enjoy unlimited access to 26 vintage pinball machines from the 1970s, '80s, and '90s, all set to free play. The museum offers a nostalgic experience with well-preserved games that transport visitors back to the heyday of pinball.
name: Myrtle Beach Pinball Museum
address: 607 27th Ave N, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: New South Brewing, established in 1998 and known as the "Beer from here," is a hidden gem located in an industrial area of Myrtle Beach. The brewery offers tours, a tasting room, and retail sales, providing visitors with the opportunity to interact with passionate brewmasters.
name: New South Brewing
address: 1109 Campbell St, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Wheels of Yesteryear Vintage Automobile Museum in Myrtle Beach is a paradise for classic car aficionados. Founded by Paul and Carol Cummings, the museum boasts a remarkable collection of over 150 American-made cars and trucks, showcasing decades of automotive history. Visitors can also explore the gift shop offering nostalgic die-cast collectibles and car-themed souvenirs.
name: Wheels of Yesteryear
address: 413 Hospitality Ln, Myrtle Beach, SC 29579, USA

excerpt: Wooden walkway along the waterfront, with shops, restaurants & amusement park rides.
detail_description: The Myrtle Beach Boardwalk and Promenade is a lively mile-long wooden walkway that runs along the waterfront, offering visitors a plethora of attractions. From seafood restaurants to amusement park rides, this oceanfront destination has something for everyone. You can take a ride on the SkyWheel, one of the largest Ferris wheels on the East Coast, or enjoy dining with a view at beachfront restaurants like Jimmy Buffett's LandShark.
name: Myrtle Beach Boardwalk and Promenade
address: Myrtle Beach, Myrtle Beach Boardwalk and Promenade, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Museum with kitschy oddities on display, including shrunken human heads & rare animal skeletons.
detail_description: Ripley's Believe It or Not! is a museum filled with quirky and unusual exhibits, such as shrunken human heads and rare animal skeletons. At the Ripley's Aquarium in Myrtle Beach, visitors can experience the thrill of traveling through the 750,000-gallon Dangerous Reef tunnel on a moving glide path surrounded by giant sharks up to 10 feet in length.
name: Ripley's Believe It or Not!
address: 901 N Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Lushly planted tiki-themed mini-golf center with 2 18-hole courses & many water features.
detail_description: Located in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina, Mt. Atlanticus Minotaur Golf is a tiki-themed mini-golf center featuring two 18-hole courses with lush landscaping and numerous water features. The course is said to be 50,000 years old and is one of the most recognizable putt-putt courses in Myrtle Beach. It boasts ancient ruins, mythical creatures, fountains, waterfalls, and various surprises and obstacles throughout the courses.
name: Mt. Atlanticus Minotaur Golf
address: 707 N Kings Hwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Myrtle Beach Watersports is a family-owned business offering a variety of water sports activities and rentals. Located just a short distance from Ocean Escape, visitors can enjoy dolphin watching tours, jet ski rentals with the option for lessons, pirate ship cruises, and pontoon boat rentals. The friendly staff provides helpful instructions for operating jet skis and ensures a smooth and enjoyable experience.
name: Myrtle Beach Watersports
address: 8201 Marina Pkwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29572, USA

detail_description: Magic Shows by Michael Bairefoot at the GTS Theatre in Myrtle Beach is a world-famous and award-winning family-friendly comedy and magic show. The 1.5-hour event promises to thrill, amaze, and entertain audiences of all ages with classic tricks brought into the new age. The intimate setting of the theater ensures that there are no bad seats, allowing for an up-close experience with mind-blowing illusions and engaging performances.
name: Magic Shows by Michael Bairefoot
address: 3237 Waccamaw Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29579, USA

detail_description: Legends Sports Pub & Grille is a popular spot on the Grand Strand, known for its award-winning live performances featuring world-class tribute artists who embody the look, sound, and character of the stars they portray. The venue offers an energetic atmosphere with dynamic choreography, a live band, and cutting-edge lighting and sound experiences. The sports-bar ambiance at Legends makes it a great place to enjoy drinks like Key Lime Pie Martini and Apple Pie Martini expertly crafted by Caleb.
name: Legends Sports Pub & Grille
address: 1410 N Ocean Blvd Suite 100, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Gay Dolphin Gift Cove is a renowned 30,000-square-foot establishment located on the Myrtle Beach Boardwalk. Since its opening in 1946, it has been a go-to destination for tourists seeking unique souvenirs and beach-themed items. With over 70,000 distinctive products spread across 50 sections known as coves, this iconic store offers everything from seashells and T-shirts to personalized bike tags and artwork.
name: Gay Dolphin Gift Cove
address: 916 N Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Explore Myrtle Beach in a unique and exciting way with Myrtle Beach Segway. Located just a short drive from Ocean Escape, they offer various options including self-guided tours at Market Common District, as well as hourly and daily rentals. Visitors rave about the North Myrtle Beach Segway Experience and the Huntington Beach State Park Tour for its informative guides and the opportunity to see alligators while gliding through the park.
name: Myrtle Beach Segway
address: 2922 Howard Ave, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Downwind Sails in Myrtle Beach offers a range of water activities for families, including parasailing for up to three people at a time and jet ski rides. They also provide banana boat rides, hobie cat rentals, ocean kayak rentals, and kite boarding lessons. Visitors have praised the friendly and knowledgeable staff who ensure a safe and enjoyable experience. Customers have enjoyed the thrilling banana boat ride to the boat before experiencing the excitement of parasailing for the first time.
name: Downwind Sails
address: 2985 S Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: EdVenture Myrtle Beach is a fantastic destination designed to ignite the imaginations of children while providing an engaging learning experience. This vibrant museum features a variety of hands-on exhibits and programs that cater to kids of all ages, from sensory play areas to the exciting firefighting Dalmatian Station. Young explorers can dive into advanced STEM concepts through interactive displays, where they can climb aboard a spaceship, experiment at mission control, and even inspect an actual airplane engine!
name: EdVenture Myrtle Beach
address: 4005 Howard Ave, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Embark on an unforgettable adventure with Blackbeard's Pirate Cruise, offering 60 to 90-minute tours aboard a themed pirate ship. Kids can transform into pirates and engage in interactive activities, including battling Bad Billy Bones with water cannons. The largest pirate ship in the Carolinas sets sail for a buccaneer experience, featuring sword-fighting, treasure hunting, and even temporary tattoos.
name: Blackbeard's Pirate Cruise
address: 141 Fantasy Harbour Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29579, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant downtown area of Myrtle Beach, Grand Strand Brewing Company, affectionately known as GSB by locals, embodies the essence of a cozy neighborhood brewery. With its inviting atmosphere and proximity to the beach, it serves as a delightful retreat from the bustling boardwalk. GSB boasts an impressive array of craft beers with playful can designs that catch your eye—think Wingtip Pilsner and Sandy Cheeks IPA.
name: Grand Strand Brewing Company
address: 819 N Kings Hwy Unit 101, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Grand Strand Plaza is a popular shopping destination in Myrtle Beach, NC. With a variety of shops, restaurants and games, it's the perfect place to spend a summer day. The air-conditioned mall is great for cooling down on hot days, and the tasty food options will satisfy any craving. Prices are high, but worth it for all the amazing finds you can make.
name: Grand Strand Plaza Shopping Center
address: 1490 S Kings Hwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: A place at the beach 1, also known as Broadway at the Beach, offers more than just shopping and fireworks. It is a hub of top-notch restaurants that cater to various tastes. From nachos to race car arcade games, this destination provides a wide array of flavors and fun for families to enjoy.
name: A place at the beach 1
address: 29577, Shore Dr, Myrtle Beach, SC 29572, USA

detail_description: Family Kingdom Parking is the perfect spot for a classic family day out in Myrtle Beach. The amusement park offers stunning views of the Atlantic Ocean and the Grand Stand from its 100-foot Ferris wheel. With over 35 rides, there's something for everyone, from thrilling experiences like the log flume water ride and the Twistn Shout steel roller coaster to more leisurely options like the Kiddie Coaster.
name: Family Kingdom Parking
address: Unnamed Road, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Sprawling outdoor entertainment center with restaurants, shopping, live shows & family attractions.
detail_description: Broadway at the Beach is a vibrant outdoor entertainment hub nestled in the heart of Myrtle Beach, covering an impressive 350 acres. This lively complex offers a delightful mix of dining, shopping, and family attractions surrounding a picturesque man-made lake. Visitors can explore an array of restaurants and bars that cater to all tastes—from casual eateries to lively nightclubs like the House of Blues and Margaritaville. The atmosphere is electric with live shows, including free summer events featuring stilt walkers and fire dancers.
name: Broadway at the Beach
address: 1325 Celebrity Cir, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: Warbird Park, located in the Market Common district of Myrtle Beach, is a free and educational attraction that pays homage to the area's military history. The park features retired aircraft such as the A-10 Warthog Thunderbolt and F-100 jet fighter, each accompanied by detailed information about their roles in past operations. Additionally, visitors can explore wooded paths, monuments honoring military heroes, and striking artwork like the metal sculpture called Warrior.
name: Warbird Park
address: Farrow Pkwy, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Fishing for mullet & trout, plus seafood dining on a wooden boardwalk with city & ocean panoramas.
detail_description: Second Ave Pier in Myrtle Beach is a picturesque spot at the south end of the Boardwalk, offering stunning views of the city and ocean. The Pier House Restaurant provides an enclosed venue with large windows for unobstructed panoramic views while dining on a variety of dishes, including seafood like Crab Cakes and Shrimp.
name: Second Ave Pier
address: South Carolina, USA

excerpt: Hip, nautical set-up for local seafood paired with wine & spirits plus happy hour & Sunday brunch.
detail_description: Hook & Barrel is a trendy seafood restaurant located in Myrtle Beach, offering a chic nautical ambiance and an extensive selection of local seafood paired with fine wines and spirits. Situated in the exclusive Dunes section of town, this upscale eatery places a strong emphasis on fresh seafood as the star of its menu. Guests can indulge in the Harvest of the Sea special, allowing them to select their preferred fresh catch, preparation style, and house-made sauce.
name: Hook & Barrel
address: 8014 N Kings Hwy B, Myrtle Beach, SC 29572, USA

excerpt: Interactive exhibits & programs for kids including a hurricane simulator, art center & gem mining.
detail_description: The Children's Museum of South Carolina is a great place for toddlers and kids of all ages to explore indoor and outdoor exhibits filled with fun technology, animals, science and nature. The museum also has a classroom where kids can learn about technology, animals, science and nature.
name: Children's Museum of South Carolina
address: 2204 N Oak St, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Down-home joint dishing up big plates of Southern comfort food like fried chicken & collard greens.
detail_description: Big Mike's Soul Food is a beloved spot in Myrtle Beach, known for its authentic Southern comfort food and warm hospitality. Named after owner and city councilman Mike Chestnut, this place offers classic Southern dishes at affordable prices. The menu includes options like fried chicken, meatloaf, collard greens, and macaroni and cheese.
name: Big Mike's Soul Food
address: 504 16th Ave N, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Global seafood & meat dishes, plus sushi, in a fashionable haunt with a rooftop bar & water views.
detail_description: Wicked Tuna at 2nd Avenue Pier is a trendy restaurant with a rooftop bar offering stunning water views. The menu features a wide variety of seafood and meat dishes, including sushi. Diners can enjoy inventive casual options like the Surf-and-Turf Burger or more upscale plates such as filet-and-lobster-tail surf and turf. The restaurant is known for its fresh sushi, indulgent seafood platters, and signature dishes like tuna tataki.
name: Wicked Tuna @ 2nd Avenue Pier
address: 110 N Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

excerpt: Laid-back American eatery with a large patio, ocean views & a menu of seafood, steak & burgers.
detail_description: Bummz Beach Cafe is a laid-back American eatery located in Myrtle Beach, offering a casual and welcoming atmosphere for beachgoers to enjoy seafood, steak, and burgers. Situated in a 1930's beach house setting with ocean views, the cafe provides a fun-filled and family-friendly experience. Guests can relax on the large patio deck with beach chairs and hammocks while sipping cocktails or indulging in tasty burgers, sandwiches, and salads.
name: Bummz Beach Cafe
address: 2002 N Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA

detail_description: If you're planning a family getaway to Myrtle Beach, make sure to include The Funplex in your itinerary! This vibrant amusement park, which opened its doors in 2021 at the northern end of the Boardwalk, is packed with excitement for all ages. With seven thrilling rides like the Sky Velocity that plunges riders six stories down and the exhilarating Up and Overboard that swings you high into the air, there's no shortage of adrenaline-pumping fun.
name: The Funplex Myrtle Beach
address: 1405 N Ocean Blvd, Myrtle Beach, SC 29577, USA
